node.text:
Our plans have changed, but our determination remains the same 🇺🇸 We might not be in Tokyo right now, but we will use this extra time to push ourselves to be citius, altius, fortius next year💪🏼

So grateful for this @poloralphlauren One-Year-Out Collection that supports @TeamUSA and helps us prepare to be our best 👊🏼

Check out the collection at the link in my bio ⭐️

node.text: Victoria gets REAL with me about her experience with binge eating, body image, and how being a college athlete can take a toll on your mental health. We talk about how she dealt with these challenges and her pathway to therapy and the help we all need from time to time. We end with some tips for performing under pressure, so you don’t want to miss that! My hope is that you all walk away with something that will help you improve your own mental health and remember you are NEVER alone!

node.title: Body Image, Mental Health & More with Victoria Garrick!

node.text: I had a little time on my hands today so I scrolled through my camera roll and threw together this video🤗 Grateful for all these times and these humans and can’t wait to make more memories! ❤️ @alixklineman @jenniferkessy & * @fiapogtenius we need some video with you! 🙈

Can always count on partner-to-coach @jenniferkessy for a balance of intensity and lightheartedness, to tell it like it is, and of course entertain us in the process 🤣 Grateful to have her on our team! 🙏🏼🙌🏼❤️ Enjoy this look at what goes on in our player box during a big match 👊🏼 (also don’t think my Gatorade matching my suit was a coincidence 💁🏼‍♀️) •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
Repost from @avpbeach

For the first time, we take you behind-the-scenes and in the coach's corner. Get an inside look at the coaching process and commentary of Olympic Silver Medalist and #AVP coach, @JenniferKessy, as she led the #ATeam into the Women's Final of the 2019 #AVPGoldSeries // Manhattan Beach Open.

Thanks @LAFC for having me! LA is 🖤&🥇😉

node.text:
A little clip of my story for @mizunovolleyballusa’s #HerOwnStory series ☺️ 

So glad I found beach and the path to continue my pro career in volleyball. There are lots of challenges on the road to success, it’s all about how you react to and navigate the adversity that determines your trajectory. I didn’t know if I was doing it “right” in the moment, I just always followed my heart, worked my 🍑 off and said yes to opportunity.

Also in honor of #WomensEqualityDay if you want to save/share this post and/or check out my ARxMizuno line that would be awesome 🛍🤗 plus there’s FREE shipping on all orders of $75+ 👊🏼 (LINK is in my bio! Or just Google - “april ross mizuno line 😉)

node.text:
The GRANDDADDY!! Manhattan Beach Open Champs!! 🏆💫🍾🎉

It was so fun to come home after the Olympics and compete at the MBO in front of a packed house for every. single. match. And to WIN! 🤯🙌🏼🙏🏼🎉 Thank you @alixklineman for being the energy leader in the final and for doing what you do! @angieakers & @fiapogtenius thank you for your dedication and time you put into coaching our team! ❤️❤️❤️

So excited to have our names going up on the Manhattan Beach Pier together again 🤗 Loved having the #ATeam out to support in person finally too! ❤️

Now for some much needed R&R 📖🧘🏼‍♀️😴😴😴

#GRATEFUL

📸: @agamephoto ⚡️

node.text:
It feels good to be back on the @AVPbeach!🏐🏝☀️

Won our first match we’ve played since the Olympics😅🎉 Gonna keep working to find our rhythm tm (and any leftover adrenaline from the Games🧐🤣) point by point! Really enjoying the homecoming and playing in front of friends, fam, and fans who cheered us on in Tokyo!🙏🏼❤️🤗

Up again tomorrow morning at 9am! 👊🏼⚔️❤️ #AVPMBO

📸: @shotbygomez ⚡️

node.text: One of my favorite things about my medals is getting to share them with all of you, so I don’t want to frame them and put them anywhere permanent, yet. But sometimes I worry they’ll get (more😬) scratched when I bring them places with me, so I asked my friend @5lbsoflove ❤️ to crochet a few pouches for them (a la @tomdaley 🙌🏼). And she OUTDID herself! I love them so much 😍 and they’re exactly what I needed, thank you Allison!🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼

node.text:
Got to REALLY celebrate our 🥇🥇 last night with more of the #ATeam! 🙌🏼🥂🎉 

It’s one of the best feelings to share this win with everyone who has supported us the whole way! 
❤️🤍💙

Now I just need to get down to Costa Mesa to celebrate with that part of the A-Team too! 🚙💨

Thanks @teddypurcell & @alixklineman for throwing such a fun bash (and making it covid safe for all of us too!👊🏼)

node.text:
What a reception! 🤗☺️🎉 

It was so great visiting the @mizunousa headquarters today and getting to celebrate with the people and company that have been supporting me for so long!🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼 I teared up when they surprised me by all wearing #ATeam shirts and cheering for me as I walked in 🥰🤗🥰 I am so grateful to be part of the Mizuno family! 

And what about that cake!! 😳😍🙌🏼🙌🏼🙌🏼

node.text:
OLYMPIC CHAMPIONS🥇!!!!!! 

Going in, it seemed like such a daunting challenge… because it is. We prepared and worked as hard as we could, but so did everyone else. Sports are uncertain, there are no guarantees. All you can do is work to foster a belief in yourself and your team, that you are capable of accomplishing your biggest dreams and then leave all you have on the court. It’s been a long, up and down road- blood, sweat, and tears; hundreds of thousands of miles flown and a few passport snaffus, but I wouldn’t change it for anything. So so so grateful it went our way and beyond happy with the result 🥇🙌🏼 but what makes me happier still is reflecting on our journey. So proud of how we stayed together and strong through it all. Proud of Alix and proud of us. And thankful for everyone else who invested in the journey with us, you guys made/make it SO much better! 🙌🏼🙏🏼❤️ #ATeam #TeamHugs

“The journey is better than the Inn.” - Cervantes #iykyk
